<item>
            <title>[HBASE-8903] Fix Thrift 2 DemoClient Python instructions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-8903</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In the DemoClient.py we have:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;# Instructions:
# 1. Run Thrift to generate the python module hbase
#    thrift --gen py ../../../src/main/resources/org/apache/hadoop/hbase/thrift2/hbase.thrift
# 2. Create a directory of your choosing that contains:
#     a. This file (DemoClient.py).
#     b. The directory gen-py/hbase (generated by instruction step 1).
# 3. pip install thrift==0.7.0
# 4. Create a table call &quot;example&quot;, with a family called &quot;family1&quot; using the hbase shell.
# 5. Start the hbase thrift2 server
#    bin/hbase thrift2 start
# 6. Execute {python DemoClient.py}.
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fix the path of the thrift definition file and Thrift version number. For the former, this works:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;$ thrift --gen py ../../../../../hbase-server/src/main/resources/org/apache/hadoop/hbase/thrift2/hbase.thrift
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Test the demo client following these instructions and make sure it all works as explained.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
